{
  "texts": [
    "For the integrated dataset, we modelled the logit (log-odds) of selecting the correct answer as a function of participant type (human vs. ChatGPT) using a Bayesian linear mixed-effects model.",
    "With ChatGPT as the baseline, the predictor was dummy coded, and the random effects structures incorporated byitem intercepts and slopes, illustrated in the subsequent formula:",
    "Furthermore, we estimated the probability of choosing the grammatical sentence for each experimental item for both ChatGPT and human participants, subsequently conducting a correlational analysis between the two sets.",
    "Echoing the methodologies of Experiment 1 and 2, we examined the extent of alignment between ChatGPT's grammatical knowledge and that of the linguists.",
    "For each pairwise phenomenon in the ChatGPT dataset, we employed five distinct analyses, summarizing instances where grammatical sentences held preference over their less grammatical counterparts."
  ]
}